Even taking the dusty, truck-filled highways sometimes rewards us with brief glimpses into the countryside scenery.#vietnam #vietnamtravel  #bikepacking

This is the first and last VXX we'll do during the dead heat of summer. Yet despite the crucible we went through today, it's impossible to regret taking the journey. #scenic #vietnam #vietnamtravel #bikepacking

Crossing from Quảng Nam into Kon Tum province means defying all reason and riding over the Annamite Mountain Range. We took the South Quang Nam road and were glad to have our near-death experience recognized in this stone inscription. #vietnam #vietnamtravel  #bikepacking

Met this pony-tailed 69 year old war vet (Montignard ethnic minority serving under the occupying US forces) at a quaint, 'country'-inspired cafe in Kon Tum. He was playing all the rock classics- Hotel California, Knocking On Heaven's Door, all the Beetles songs, etc. Despite the deep historical and political cleavages that run throughout Việt Nam, it's impossible not to make friends and share stories with everyone we meet. #vietnam  #vietnamtravel  #bikepacking #classicrock

"For the last five hundred to one thousand years in China, Japan, Korea, and Tibet, Gohas been known as one of the “Four Great Accomplishments” that any cultured person should master. The other three are painting, music, and calligraphy. The techniques for success for all four are often couched in the same Daoist language. Unlike the other three, however, Go involves the desires for advancement of two people. Because there is another person involved as an opponent—or partner—the question of whether to take smaller profits now or build up influence for possibly greater gains later on in the game is constantly arising. The process of accurately intuiting, calculating and judging what you want and what the person across the board wants is what the balance and harmony of Go are all about." -Go More Than A Game #saigon #hochiminhcity #igo #cafe #vietnam #covay
